A crash involving three trucks on the N3 near Mooi River in KwaZulu-Natal on Sunday night ended with residents looting even stationary trucks. It is alleged a truck broke down on the northbound before Mooi River toll gate and another truck crashed into it and caught fire. The load from the broken down truck spilled onto the roadway and people started looting. It is alleged other stationary trucks were also looted. The road was backed up until late on Sunday. All lanes were open by Monday morning and the trucks will be recovered during the day. Meanwhile, another truck was looted near Umkomaas Valley. The truck had overturned and residents started looting the truck. It is alleged security officials who were at the scene and police were outnumbered by residents who could not be controlled.